description:
Baron Zemo and Bucky – two characters linked through history whether they like it or not. And now Zemo has set his sights on Bucky and plans to destroy our new Captain America one step at a time.

Also, Iron Man and War Machine are holding the bag after the Tokyo attacks make Detroit Steel look like a hero! As Tony, Rhodey and Hill get to the bottom of who masterminded the terror attempt, the fledgling company Stark Resilent takes its first baby steps toward growth…and Tony draws a link between Hammer Industries and an old foe that almost killed him!

Plus, cover your ears and gird your loins for the four-letter word that changes everything for Thor, for Asgard and for Earth: O.D.I.N! And you won't believe who Ol' One Eye brings back with him. On top of that, the God of Thunder has to deal with the ramifications of reincarnating Loki, the least of which are that the God of Tricks has taken a form no one saw coming. If that wasn't enough, the town of Broxton has to deal with the refugees of nine worlds, on the run and terrified, as the World Eaters continue their trans-universal rampage of madness!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America #607, Thor VOL.1 #618 and Invincible Iron Man Vol. 5#28!

The conclusion to ‘Dark Son’! It's brother versus brother! Skaar battles Hiro-Kala as the planet K'ai hurtles towards a catastrophic collision with Earth! Can hulk save the world - and both his sons?

by Greg Pak, Jay Leisten, Scott Hanna, Vic Drujiniu and Barry Kitson.

Also: When they last met, the Red Hulk defeated Thor in a titanic struggle! But now the thunder god is back - and he wants some payback!

By Jeff Parker, Mark Robinson and Gabriel Hardman.

Includes material reprinted from Incredible Hulks #617 and Hulk #26-27.

New story! Wolverine and Spider-Man find themselves up to their eyeballs in ape people, Robot dinosaurs and angry planets!

By Jason Aaron and Adam Kubert.

Also: Deadpool takes on Ceres and his vicious vampire cult! Get ready for some undead craziness!

By Daniel Way and Bong Dazo.

Includes material reprinted from Astonishing Spider-Man & Wolverine #1-2 and Deadpool #31.

Big Time Concludes!

It’s the ultimate battle as Spider-Man takes on the NEW Scorpion!

Also, witness the birth of a new Spider-Man in the start of a brand-new story arc! Bonded to the dangerous and powerful Venom symbiote, this new webslinger is showing Peter Parker up in the hero department!

Plus, the psychotic symbiote Carnage is about to make the greatest return from the dead since Lazarus (or Bucky)! And it’s all down to billionaire industrialist, Michael Hall! The question is how… and more importantly why!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #654-654.1 and Carnage #2!

Investigating the murder of a teenage girl, Cage suddenly learns that a three-way gang war is under way for control of the turf he calls home. And what better way to disrupt the stalemate than offering his services to the highest bidder?
name: TPB

description:
When Gary Hampton is mauled and left for dead, his life takes a drastic turn. Gary is cursed. When the moon is full, he transforms into a beast of the night: a werewolf. This curse will not be used for evil - witness the birth of the world's most unlikely new superhero: WOLF-MAN! Brought to you by the writer of THE WALKING DEAD and INVINCIBLE!

Collects The Astounding Wolf-Man #1-7.
name: Vol. 1

description: After the Earth-Shattering events of volume one we find Gary Hampton, The Astounding Wolf-Man on the run from the law - his very life hanging in the balance. He must learn how to harness the beast within - once and for all - and clear his name before the full might of the U.S. government takes him down. Guest-starring INVINCIBLE! Collects The Astounding Wolf-Man #8-12 and Invincible #57.
name: Vol. 2

description: Locked down! Gary Hampton, the Astounding Wolf-Man has been tried and convicted of murder! Now, locked away in Stronghold Prison he comes face to face with the very enemies he put away. Also in this volume, the villainy of The Face! Collects The Astounding Wolf-Man #13-18.
name: Vol. 3

description: THIS IS THE END! The elder's master plan is revealed! Zechariah's final fate is decided! Wolf-Man's astounding adventure comes to a close. Every moment from the beginning of the series to now has been leading to this. After this volume, the world of the Astounding Wolf-Man will never be the same again! Collects The Astounding Wolf-Man #19-25.

description:
Addidas is a bright and quirky young girl who spends most of her time helping her widowed father in his job as a chimney sweep in the industrial metropolis they live in. When Addidas ventures too far into a chimney, she encounters a bizarre new friend...

From prolific independent European creators Wazem and Peeters comes a colorful and poetic tale that brilliantly balances its fantastical elements with poignant, realistic themes.
